          <OMSTR>&quot;. The constants 0,1,2,3,.. etc have their usual meaning. For this exercise the word &quot;number&quot; will mean &quot;natural number&quot;. Translate each of the following statements into grammatically correct English that doesn&apos;t use any variables, formal symbols, or mathematical notation.  Type your answer for each statement after the : following the statement. After stating the statement in English say whether or not it is true.  If it is a true existence (or unique existence) statement give an example of a number that shows it is true.  If it is a false for-all statement give a counterexample, i.e., a number that shows it is false.  Note that you don&apos;t have to give examples when it is a false existence statement or a true for-all statement.</OMSTR>
